<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 10:23PM EDT  by NWS Indianapolis</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Hendricks and southwestern Marion Counties through 1045 PM EDT...
At 1022 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brownsburg, or 12 miles west of Indianapolis, moving southeast at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Speedway around 1030 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
